HEADWORD: Sideways
<hw>Side"ways`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Toward the side;
sidewise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A second refraction made <qex>sideways</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir I.
Newton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His beard, a good palm's length, at least, . . . ⟦br⟧
Shot <qex>sideways</qex>, like a swallow's wings.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

